text:
The four-gill fellow, we’ll set him clattering,  
And christen him with steaming water;  
Then we’ll sit us down and take our whitter,  
To warm the heart;  
And faith, we’ll be better acquainted  
Before we part.

source_text:
The four-gill chap, we’se gar him clatter,
An’ kirsen him wi’ reekin water;
Syne we’ll sit down an’ tak our whitter,
To cheer our heart;
An’ faith, we’se be acquainted better
Before we part.
